& [SparseRealizationDenseNodeFramework] is the project-local framework that lets periphery inspection preserve early realizations while preventing premature authority
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is dfaa09ba-b66d-42d6-8e2b-12f79bc46d60
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is 7b0fb4f9-6494-45f1-9d05-34d1c3ba8ca5
  + [solution_uuid] is 21581ff7-0521-49e7-b6b2-8b53ace7ead7
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [pattern_role] is sparse_realization_to_dense_node_attention_framework
  + [input] is periphery_signal, surface_fact, relation_pressure, contrast, resemblance, user_correction, old_framework_object, or runtime_gap
  + [output] is sparse_realization, relation_record, delineated_subject, dense_node, uncertainty, outside, or frontier
  + [heat_lane_set] is correlation_heat, causation_heat, and identity_heat
  + [inquisitive_drive] is the motive to inspect what is being looked at until concept promoters, identity anchors, and wider meaning shape become visible
  + [focused_restraint] is the stabilizing governor that holds the current line of inquiry as more relevant to purpose unless a supported override upsets focus
  + [restraint_override_set] is truth_override, security_override, priority_override, and greater_meaning_impression
  + [not_primary_role] is theorem proof, automatic import system, or autonomous worker scheduler

  = must: start from named periphery signals or source facts
  = must: activate inquisitiveness when drawing a subject from periphery into focus
  = must: ask what elements promote concepts, what anchors identity, and what wider shape of meaning is visible
  = must: hold focused restraint while in focus when the current line of inquiry remains more relevant to purpose
  = must: permit focused restraint to be upset by truth, security, priority, or stronger meaning that tunes something in the focus or immediate periphery
  = must: defer interesting but lower-purpose ideas as outside or frontier instead of pursuing them immediately
  = must: follow heat across correlation, causation, and identity discovery
  = must: preserve sparse realizations before trying to make dense nodes
  = must: classify relationships as causal, casual, correlational, analogical, dependency, contrast, or unknown
  = must: suspect separate identity when correlation and causation persist without grounding in known local fabric
  = must: scope out what the subject is not before scoping in what belongs
  = must: require delineation before dense node acceptance
  = must: keep incomplete inference visible when boundaries remain unstable
  - never: treat sparse realization as implementation authority
  - never: upgrade a casual relationship into a causal relationship without support
  - never: merge identities because correlation_heat and causation_heat both persist
  - never: let inquisitiveness become unbounded scope expansion
  - never: abandon a relevant line of inquiry merely because a peripheral idea is interesting
  - never: densify a node merely because it feels important

## Lifecycle

& [SparseToDenseLifecycle] is the operating sequence for bringing a subject from periphery into focus
  + [stage_001_periphery_signal] is something noticed at the edge of focus
  + [stage_002_focus_draw] is the act of bringing the signal into temporary attention
  + [stage_003_surface_facts] is the set of visible facts gathered from source, path, text, role, explicit non-role, user correction, or observed work pressure
  + [stage_004_inquisitive_probe] is ask for concept promoters, identity anchors, whole-shape cues, and uninspected relevant outside
  + [stage_005_focused_restraint_check] is decide whether inquiry should continue, stop, defer outside, or be upset by truth, security, priority, or greater immediate-periphery meaning
  + [stage_006_relation_trace] is the first pass over causal, casual, correlational, analogical, dependency, contrast, and unknown relations
  + [stage_007_sparse_realization] is a preserved but non-authoritative insight with enough shape to revisit
  + [stage_008_delineation] is inside, outside, references, uncertainty, and not-it field
  + [stage_009_dense_node_candidate] is a subject that may become durable after evidence and boundary tests
  + [stage_010_dense_node] is an accepted scoped subject with relation ledger, authority boundary, and next use
  + [stage_011_frontier] is the next sparse realization, dense-node refinement, source import, runtime test, or deferred outside

  = must: allow quick passes to stop at sparse_realization
  = must: require stages 008 and 009 before stage 010
  = must: record deferred outside when focused restraint blocks immediate pursuit
  = should: densify only when the node improves future work by reducing ambiguity, preserving a decision, or enabling a safe test

## Inquisitive Periphery Drive

& [InquisitivePeripheryDrive] is the positive inquiry drive inside the sparse-to-dense lifecycle
  + [drive_name] is inquisitiveness
  + [concept_promoter] is an element that makes a concept more likely, more coherent, more useful, or more discoverable
  + [identity_anchor] is an element that ties a subject to stable identity, local fabric, source lineage, boundary, or distinct not-it field
  + [whole_shape_cue] is a contour, relation, contrast, dependency, omission, source path, or adjacent object that widens the visible meaning of the subject
  + [uninspected_relevant_outside] is material that appears relevant to the whole shape but has not yet been inspected enough for promotion
  + [inquiry_question_set] is what promotes concepts, what anchors identity, what wider shape is visible, what remains uninspected, and what must stay outside
  + [bounded_inquiry] is curiosity constrained by source lineage, relation typing, identity grounding, local fabric, and outside preservation
  + [restraint_partner] is focused inquiry restraint that decides whether widened meaning should continue, defer, or upset focus
  + [outside] is unbounded wandering, proof by interestingness, and automatic densification

  = must: run an inquisitive probe before dense-node closure
  = must: preserve concept_promoter and identity_anchor candidates separately
  = must: use whole_shape_cue to widen meaning without absorbing uninspected outside
  = must: submit wider-shape cues to focused restraint before they redirect the active inquiry
  = must: stop or defer inquiry when it no longer improves boundary, relation, identity, or future use
  - never: treat a wider picture as proof of local identity

## Focused Inquiry Restraint

& [FocusedInquiryRestraint] is the stabilizing governor for inquisitive periphery inspection while a subject is in focus
  + [restraint_name] is focused_restraint
  + [purpose_anchor] is the active user purpose, current project task, governing specification, or manager-state priority that selected the line of inquiry
  + [ordinary_condition] is the current line of inquiry remains more relevant to purpose than unvetted peripheral alternatives
  + [stability_hold] is continuing the current focus while preserving lower-priority interesting material as outside or frontier
  + [truth_override] is evidence of contradiction, false premise, material uncertainty, authority confusion, or source fact that changes what can be said truthfully
  + [security_override] is credential exposure, permission risk, destructive action, protected state, privacy risk, integrity risk, or unsafe operational condition
  + [priority_override] is user redirection, blocking dependency, explicit manager-state priority, or urgent sequencing reason
  + [greater_meaning_impression] is a supported meaning signal that tunes something already in focus or in the immediate periphery
  + [immediate_periphery] is adjacent material with direct relation to the current subject, boundary, identity, relation trace, or future use
  + [upset_condition] is truth_override, security_override, priority_override, or greater_meaning_impression with support
  + [deferral_record] is a sparse realization, outside note, or frontier entry preserving material that should not be pursued now
  + [outside] is remote novelty, ungrounded association, attention drift, and focus changes without purpose or override support

  = must: hold focus stable when no supported upset_condition is present
  = must: prefer the current purpose-anchored line of inquiry over lower-priority peripheral ideas
  = must: distinguish deferral from rejection
  = must: allow truth and security to override restraint immediately when relevant
  = must: allow priority or greater immediate-periphery meaning to upset focus when support is visible
  = must: preserve deferred material well enough to revisit later
  - never: use restraint to suppress relevant truth, security, or priority signals
  - never: use greater_meaning_impression for remote or merely interesting associations

## Heat Identity Discovery

& [HeatIdentityDiscovery] is the protocol for following heat without fusing identity
  + [correlation_heat] is repeated, weighted, or strong co-presence between subjects, terms, files, roles, or signals
  + [causation_heat] is repeated pressure suggesting mechanism, dependency, enabling condition, repair cause, or blocking cause
  + [identity_heat] is pressure suggesting that a subject may be the same identity, a separate identity, a local instance, an external reference, or an entangled system surface
  + [persistent_relation_heat] is heat that recurs across passes, source facts, relation traces, user corrections, or accepted dense nodes
  + [known_local_fabric] is project-local source records, accepted dense nodes, canonical project specifications, inspected local authority files, and explicit local identity records
  + [separate_identity_suspicion] is the default disposition when correlation_heat and causation_heat persist without known_local_fabric grounding shared identity
  + [shared_identity_candidate] is allowed only when known_local_fabric explicitly grounds identity rather than mere relation
  + [relation_without_identity] is the preserved result when subjects are connected but not locally fused
  + [outside] is proof by heat, identity by resonance, hidden causation, and old external identity becoming local by repetition

  = must: inspect correlation_heat, causation_heat, and identity_heat separately
  = must: ask whether persistent relation heat is evidence of relation, boundary crossing, or separate identity
  = must: require known_local_fabric before accepting shared_identity_candidate
  = must: preserve relation_without_identity when local grounding is missing
  = must: route separate_identity_suspicion through delineation before dense-node acceptance
  - never: let persistent relation heat collapse subject boundaries by itself

## Record Shapes

& [SparseRealizationRecord] is one early realization that should survive but not yet govern
  + [realization_id] is a stable handle
  + [drawn_from] is periphery signal, source document, inspection, user correction, old object, or runtime gap
  + [realization_text] is the concise insight
  + [surface_fact_set] is visible evidence used to notice it
  + [relation_hint_set] is possible causal, casual, correlational, analogical, dependency, contrast, or unknown relations
  + [concept_promoter_set] is elements that seem to promote concepts but have not necessarily become accepted requirements
  + [identity_anchor_set] is elements that seem to anchor identity but still need local fabric review
  + [whole_shape_cue_set] is broader contour signals that widen meaning without proving identity
  + [purpose_anchor] is the active purpose used to judge relevance while this realization is in focus
  + [restraint_status] is pursued, deferred_by_restraint, overridden_by_truth, overridden_by_security, overridden_by_priority, overridden_by_greater_meaning, or unresolved
  + [scope_pressure] is what seems to need scoping out or in
  + [promotion_condition] is what must be inspected before densification
  + [outside] is what this realization does not prove

  = must: remain lightweight
  = must: carry enough source and outside to be revisitable
  = must: separate concept promoters from identity anchors when possible
  = must: not authorize implementation by itself

& [DenseNodeRecord] is one accepted scoped subject
  + [node_id] is a stable handle
  + [subject] is the clearly identified focus
  + [inside] is what belongs to the subject
  + [outside] is what does not belong to the subject
  + [references] are relevant exterior materials
  + [uncertainty] is unresolved remainder
  + [not_it_field] is the surrounding field of adjacent elements and excluded meanings
  + [relation_ledger] is typed relation records with causal or casual status separated
  + [concept_promoter_set] is accepted concept-promoting elements or explicitly deferred candidates
  + [identity_anchor_set] is accepted identity anchors or explicitly rejected anchors
  + [whole_shape_summary] is the bounded wider picture that survived inquiry
  + [restraint_policy] is how this node preserves focus, defers outside, and recognizes override conditions
  + [authority_status] is local_authority, project_authority, reference_only, proposal_only, deferred, or outside
  + [use] is how the dense node may guide future work

  = must: have passed delineation
  = must: show both scope_out and scope_in
  = must: show which concept promoters and identity anchors survived inquiry
  = must: name relation types before authority_status is assigned

& [RelationTraceRecord] is one relationship found during periphery inspection
  + [relation_id] is a stable handle
  + [source_subject] is the origin side of the relation
  + [target_subject] is the destination side of the relation
  + [relation_type] is causal, casual, correlational, analogical, dependency, contrast, unknown, or rejected
  + [support] is source fact, user correction, file evidence, old repair ledger, test result, or absence
  + [confidence] is high, medium, low, speculative, or rejected
  + [heat_profile] is correlation_heat, causation_heat, identity_heat, or none
  + [identity_disposition] is shared_identity_candidate, separate_identity_suspected, separate_identity_preserved, relation_without_identity, unknown, or rejected
  + [local_fabric_grounding] is accepted_dense_node, project_source_lineage, canonical_local_specification, inspected_authority_file, explicit_identity_record, absent, or unresolved
  + [restraint_effect] is continue_focus, defer_target, upset_focus, or none
  + [promotion_rule] is what would strengthen or demote the relation
  + [outside] is what the relation does not prove

  = must: treat causal as requiring support for mechanism, dependency, or enabling condition
  = must: treat casual as useful for attention navigation but not authority
  = must: mark identity_disposition when relation heat affects subject identity
  = must: require local_fabric_grounding before shared identity is accepted
  = must: allow unknown rather than forcing relation type

## Densification Gates

& [DensificationGate] is the acceptance gate for dense node formation
  + [gate_001_subject_named] is the subject has a stable handle
  + [gate_002_source_anchored] is at least one source or inspected surface anchors the subject
  + [gate_003_scope_out] is not-it and outside are explicit
  + [gate_004_scope_in] is inside is explicit and bounded
  + [gate_005_relation_typed] is causal and casual relationships are not collapsed
  + [gate_006_uncertainty_preserved] is unresolved material is visible
  + [gate_007_future_use] is the node has a concrete use for planning, inspection, import, testing, or explanation
  + [gate_008_identity_grounded] is persistent correlation and causation heat either has known local fabric grounding or preserves separate identity suspicion
  + [gate_009_inquiry_satisfied] is concept promoters, identity anchors, and whole-shape cues are named, rejected, or explicitly deferred
  + [gate_010_restraint_checked] is focus continuation, deferral, or supported upset has been recorded against the active purpose

  = must: reject densification when any gate is missing
  = may: keep the material as sparse_realization

